These small droids are widespread.  The term "utility droid" is used for many different models that vary widely in form and function. Some of them, particularly the Duwani Mechanicals models, were at times referred as "astromech droids." 

Some models are used for advanced applied physics functions such as starship repair, astrogation, and even computer slicing and programming. Others perform more menial tasks such as janitorial duties and waste disposal.

Almost all are under one meter tall. They arre equipped either with wheeled legs or small repulsorlift generators for movement.

The Jedi Temple Guards are a special sect of Jedi sworn to guardianship over not only the Order but over locales deemed sacred or integral to the balance of the Force. The sect is shrouded deep in mystery, its members leaving behind their past names and identities entirely to serve its cause as faceless defenders.

Beyond temple grounds, the activities of the Temple Guards are highly classified, but what few rumors the Jedi indulge in speak of everything from routine scouting, to spying and infiltration of potential enemies.

A good sauce pan is every cook's friend.  Both for boiling potatoes, and restoring order. Grab this pan, open one can of whoop-ass, and do lunch!

Guests to the temple and its grounds must keep their weapons stowed unless given leave by a Jedi Knight.

Guests are welcome, but are expected to be respectful and not to interrupt ongoing lessons.

Do not disturb the Temple Guards from their duties.

Non-Jedi must be accompanied by at least one Jedi of Padawan or higher standing to enter the Temple interior.

Those seeking knowledge of the Order to join its ranks should speak to any active member.
For those experienced and trained, these walls can be used to run across and jump.
